original_result.user_prompt: What's VT100 code to render green terminal text?
original_result.completion_text:
The VT100 is a computer terminal that uses ANSI escape codes to control various aspects of the terminal display, including colors. To render green text in a VT100-compatible terminal, you can use the following ANSI escape sequence:

`\033[32mGreen Text\033[0m`

Here's an example demonstrating this in practice:

```
\033[32mHello, Green World!\033[0m
```

When executed in a VT100-compatible terminal, the word "Hello, Green World!" will appear in green color. Remember that `\033` represents the ESC (Escape) character, `[` starts the color code, `32` specifies the bright green color, and finally, `m` ends the escape sequence. The termination code `\033[0m` resets the text formatting back to default, ensuring only the desired portion appears colored.
